collection:
We may actively or automatically collect, use, store, or transfer
your Personal Data, which may include, without limitation, the following:

  * Personal identification information such as name, email, phone number, nationality, date of birth, address, and government identification information;

  * Institutional details such as corporate legal name, corporate registration information, government identification number, proof of identity and legal existence, address, business description, and beneficial owner information;

  * Commercial information such as data related to transactions conducted on the OKX Platform;

  * Financial information such as credit/debit card numbers and bank account information;

  * Correspondence Information such as communication with our Customer Support team and response to user survey;

  * Information required by regulatory agencies such as state and federal licensing authorities and consumer protection agencies; and

  * Other identifiers such as device fingerprint data, IP address, and geolocation information.

sharing:
** OKX may transfer your
Personal Data from Hong Kong to a jurisdiction or territory outside Hong Kong
on any of the following grounds:

  * OKX has reasonable grounds for believing that there is in force in that jurisdiction or territory any law which is substantially similar to, or serves the same purposes as the PDPO;

  * you have consented in writing to such transfer (which you hereby grant if you have not previously done so);

  * OKX has reasonable grounds for believing that, in all the circumstances of the case:

(a) such transfer is for the avoidance or mitigation of adverse action against
you;

(b) it is not practicable to obtain your written consent to such transfer; and

(c) if it was practicable to obtain such consent, you would give it;

  * your Personal Data is exempt from data protection principle 3 (as defined in Schedule 1 to the PDPO) by virtue of an exemption under Part 8 of the PDPO.

**D. Disclosure of personal information outside of Australia**

We may send your information overseas, including to (amongst others):

  * service providers or third parties who store data or operate outside Australia;

  * liquidity providers to complete international transactions;

  * organisations we partner with to provide products and services; and

  * government or law enforcement agencies to comply with laws and assist them.
